@justalexoki I grew up in a nonreligious household in a militantly atheistic society, although there were strong basics of Christianity in my grandparents' generation. I converted out of my own conviction as an adult, spurred by many personal and general crises through which I had gone through, and finding the answer to most of the deep life problems I had to deal with after reading the Bible. The choice of Catholicism for me was in a small part due to the cultural reasons, but more based on the witness of many wonderful friends and family members that I loved and admired. 

I have many good evangelical friends, and in general don't have any major issues with Evangelicalism. IMHO, decision which path to walk comes down to your sincere discernment of which way you can grow closer to God and which way He is calling you to walk. 

Happy to talk more about these matters. DMs open.

